Welcome to my website!
Hello and welcome. My name is Anthony Nunnery and this is my webpage. I am currently a full-time research assistant at the Mandel School of Applied Social Science enrolled in the CWRU’s School of Medicine Masters in Biostatistics program. In the future, this website will be a good way to connect with and follow me on my career journey. Thank you for your time and be well!

title: Education
text: Anthony graduated from Bonnabel High School in May 2017. Anthony spent his time at Bonnabel being educated like any other student and engaging with cross country and band for extracurricular activities. Since then he has not picked up a pair of running shoes and neither an instrument.

title: Experience
text:
Anthony is currently a Research Assistant 2 working under Dr. Margaret Baughman, at the Mandel School of Applied Social Science. He can be found at the school’s research commons area M-F during most of the week when not conducting field interviews for various addiction recovery related research projects.
